						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the wall of a house.</p>						

						<p>Dēvarāya I, 1409 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1331, Vīrōdhin,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1409 A.D.,</hi> the other details being lost.</p>						

						<p>The record mentions an Oḍeya as ruling in Vijayanagara. The date falls in the reign of Dēvarāya I.</p>						

						</summary>
